    Skip backup of logical BMC path
    
    The logical BMC path contains the MAC addresses (eth0 and eth1) of the
    local BMC.
    
    In redundant BMC systems, during failover the new active BMC restores
    the data from backup path to PIM path. This commit adds a check to skip
    copy of logical BMC path, to avoid syncing MAC address across redundant
    BMCs.
    
    This ensures each BMC retains its own MAC addresses and prevents
    network conflicts during failover.
    
